  number of annual leave days for a full year (that information
  appears elsewhere in the Staff Rules / Article 27). If you want the
  exact number, check the full Staff Rules or Article 27 of the
  Conditions of Employment.  - Pro rata if not a full year: If you do
  not work a full year, your leave entitlement is calculated pro rata,
  using an average of 21 working days per month (rounded up to the
  nearest half hour).  - Minimum leave to be taken during the calendar
  year: You must take at least 20 days of annual leave before the end
  of the calendar year; that minimum must include at least one period
  of two consecutive weeks.  - Carry‑over to the following year:   -
  You may carry over a maximum of 10.5 days of annual leave each year.
  - If, for business requirements or personal reasons, you have not
  taken the required minimum of 20 days by year‑end, you may (with
